{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Uses a geometry object to choose a sop from which the channels will be created."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["The Geometry CHOP uses a geometry object to choose a SOP from which the\nchannels will be created. The channels are created from the point\nattributes of a SOP, such as the X, Y and Z of the point position."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["The SOP can select a subset of the points using Point Groups. The set of\nattributes that are converted to channels are chosen using the names of\nthe attributes seen on the Info pop-up of SOP tiles."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["This CHOP works in tandem with the ", {"text": ["Geometry >"], "type": "em"}, " ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Channel\n        SOP"], "value": "/nodes/sop/channel", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/channel", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}, ". Point data can be modified in CHOPs and\n        then fed back to SOPs through the Channel SOP, therefore be sure\n        to take a look at the Channel SOP description."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["See the Channel SOP"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Retrieves the geometry from the SOP pointed to by this path."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["SOP"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Fetch only the points within this point group. If blank, all points are fetched."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Group"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The geometry fetch method."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Creates one channel for each attribute, and all points\n        use this channel (the first point resides at index 0,\n        the next at 1, and so on). The length of the channels\n        will be the number of points fetched."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": ["Static"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Creates one channel per attribute per point. The\n        channels show the animation of each point\u2019s\n        position/attribute values."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": ["Animated"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Method"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["A string list of attributes to fetch from the SOP. The common attributes are:"]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Point position (X, Y, Z) - 3 values."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": [{"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Point weight with a value of 1."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": [{"text": ["Pw"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Point color (red, green, blue) - 3 values."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": [{"text": ["Cd"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Point alpha with a value of 1."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": [{"text": ["Alpha"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Point normal value (X, Y, Z) - 3 values."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": [{"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["point texture coordinates (U,V,W) - 3 values."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": [{"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Attribute Scope"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The names to use for the newly fetched attributes. There must be one name per attribute, so an attribute scope of ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, " should have a rename scope with three names (like tx ty tz)."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Rename Scope"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies a point integer attribute to use as bitmask based of rename scope index."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["If the rename scope is set to \"tx ty tz\", the first 3 bits of the integer determines which channels are created."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["tx bit is activated by a value of 1."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["ty bit is activated by a value of 2."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["tz bit is activated by a value of 4."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["A value of 3 means the tx and ty bits are active."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["A value of 5 means the tx and tz bits are active."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["A value of 6 means the ty and tz bits are active."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": ["A value of 7 means the tx,ty,tz bits are active."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["This only applies to ", {"text": ["Animated"], "type": "ui"}, " Method."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Filter by Attribute"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["If a transform object is specified, the point values will be represented relative to that object\u2019s origin and rotation."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Transform Object"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Rebuilds the fetched channels by the value of this attribute. A common example is the ", {"text": ["id"], "type": "code"}, " attribute found in particles. A channel is built for each unique id since the number of points may vary."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["This only applies to ", {"text": ["Animated"], "type": "ui"}, " Method."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Organize by Attribute"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 5, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies a point string attribute to use as a prefix when building channel names. Without this, channels are named by appending the point index. This makes it possible to use a single CHOP node to export point attributes to node parameters."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["This only applies to ", {"text": ["Animated"], "type": "ui"}, " Method."]}], "indent": 5, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Point Name Attribute"]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Geometry"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Indicates how much of the channel to cook."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["All of the current global animation range."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": ["Use Full Animation Range"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Only the sample at the current frame."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": ["Use Current Frame"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Specify the range using the Start/End parameters."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "text": ["Use Start/End"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Channel Range"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The time range over which to fetch the geometry values when ", {"text": ["Animated"], "type": "ui"}, " Method is selected."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Start/End"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/start /end"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The sample rate to use for the fetched channels."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Sample Rate"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/rate"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The extend condition before the channel\u2019s beginning."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Extend Left"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The extend condition after the channel\u2019s ending."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Extend Right"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The value of the default value extend condition."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Default Value"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/defval"}, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Some of these parameters may not be available on all CHOP nodes."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["To determine which channels get affected, some CHOPs have a scope string. Patterns can be used in the scope, for example ", {"text": ["*"], "type": "code"}, " (match all), and ", {"text": ["?"], "type": "code"}, " (match single character). "]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The following are examples of possible channel name matching options:"]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches a single channel name."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["chan2"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches four channel names, separated by spaces."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["chan3 tx ty tz"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches each channel that starts with ", {"text": ["chan"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["chan*"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches each channel that has ", {"text": ["foot"], "type": "code"}, " in it."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["*foot*"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The ", {"text": ["?"], "type": "code"}, " matches a single character. ", {"text": ["t?"], "type": "code"}, " matches two-character channels starting with t.  "]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["t?"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches channels ", {"text": ["rx"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["ry"], "type": "code"}, " and ", {"text": ["rz"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["r[xyz]"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches number ranges giving ", {"text": ["blend3"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["blend5"], "type": "code"}, ", and ", {"text": ["blend7"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["blend[3-7:2]"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Matches channels ", {"text": ["blend2"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["blend3"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["blend5"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["blend13"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["blend[2-3,5,13]"], "type": "code"}]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"text": ["[xyz]"], "type": "code"}, "matches three characters, giving channels ", {"text": ["tx"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["ty"], "type": "code"}, " and ", {"text": ["tz"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": [{"text": ["t[xyz]"], "type": "code"}]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scope"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The Sample Rate Match Options handle cases where multiple input CHOPs\u2019 sample rates are different."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use rate of first input to resample others."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Resample At First Input\u2019s Rate"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Resample to highest sample rate."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Resample At Maximum Rate"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Resample to the lowest sample rate."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Resample At Minimum Rate"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Does not accept conflicting sample rates."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Error if Rates Differ"]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sample Rate Match"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The units for which time parameters are specified."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For example, you can specify the amount of time a lag should last for in seconds (default), frames (at the Houdini FPS), or samples (in the CHOP\u2019s sample rate)."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["When you change the Units parameter, it does not convert the existing parameters to the new units."]}], "role": "item", "indent": 4, "type": "note"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "note_group"}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Units"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Time Slicing is a feature which boosts cooking performance and reduces memory usage. Traditionally, CHOPs calculate the channel over its entire frame range. If the channel does need to be evaluated every frame, then cooking the entire range of the channel is unnecessary. It is more efficient to calculate only the fraction of the channel that is needed. This fraction is known as a Time Slice."]}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Time Slice"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Causes the memory consumed by a CHOP to be released after it is cooked and the data passed to the next CHOP."]}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Unload"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The Export prefix is prepended to CHOP channel names to determine where to export to. "]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For example, if the CHOP channel was named ", {"text": ["geo1:tx"], "type": "code"}, ", and the prefix was ", {"text": ["/obj"], "type": "code"}, ", the channel would be exported to ", {"text": ["/obj/geo1/tx"], "type": "code"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can leave the ", {"text": ["Export Prefix"], "type": "ui"}, " blank, but then your CHOP track names need to be absolute paths, such as ", {"text": ["obj:geo1:tx"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "role": "item", "indent": 4, "type": "note"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "note_group"}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Export Prefix"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Every CHOP has this option. Each CHOP gets a default color assigned for display in the Graph port, but you can override the color in the Common page under Graph Color. There are 36 RGB color combinations in the Palette."]}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Graph Color"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When the graph displays the animation curves and a CHOP has two or more channels, this defines the difference in color from one channel to the next, giving a rainbow spectrum of colors."]}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Graph Color Step"]}], "type": "parameters_item_group", "container": true}], "container": true, "level": 3, "text": ["Common"], "indent": 0, "type": "h", "id": "common"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Channel"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/nodes/chop/export", "fullpath": "/nodes/chop/export", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/nodes/chop/fetch", "fullpath": "/nodes/chop/fetch", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/nodes/chop/image", "fullpath": "/nodes/chop/image", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/nodes/chop/particle", "fullpath": "/nodes/chop/particle", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/nodes/chop/shuffle", "fullpath": "/nodes/chop/shuffle", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["Geometry"], "summary": ["Uses a geometry object to choose a sop from which the channels will be created."], "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "geometry", "context": "chop", "type": "node", "icon": "CHOP/geometry"}, "included": ["/nodes/chop/common.txt"], "type": "root"}